# SSM-Transcriber ‚Äî Cursor Rules

Full roadmap: docs/PLAN.md

## Language & Runtime
- Python 3.12 (pinned via `.python-version`). Use `X | Y` union syntax, not `Optional[X]`.
- **Sync through Phase 4.** No `async def` on pipeline, source, provider, or formatter methods ‚Äî every library in the stack (`ffmpeg-python`, `yt-dlp`, `faster-whisper`, google SDKs) is blocking-native. Revisit at Phase 5. See `docs/PLAN.md` ‚Üí Phase 1 Foundations F1.
- Package manager: `uv`. Never suggest `pip install` directly.
- Entry point: `uv run ssm-transcriber`

## Code style
- Line length: 100 chars (ruff enforced)
- Imports: stdlib ‚Üí third-party ‚Üí local, blank line between groups
- Type hints required on all function signatures
- Pydantic v2: use `model_config = ConfigDict(...)`, not inner `class Config`

## Architecture rules (Phase 1 Foundations ‚Äî see docs/PLAN.md)
- Config access: always `from transcriber.config import settings`, never `os.environ`
- Never log secrets ‚Äî use `settings.redacted_dump()` for diagnostics (F8)
- Provider names never hardcoded in pipeline logic ‚Äî only in registry + settings validator
- Sources return `PreparedMedia` (F2); the pipeline never sees raw URIs
- `RunWorkspace` per CLI invocation, `try/finally` cleanup, atomic output writes (F5)
- Cache keys are **versioned composites**: audio hash + provider id + model id + model revision + language + VAD mode + schema version. Never `SHA256(file + quality)` (F3)
- VAD is a sidecar ‚Äî canonical transcription runs on full audio; VAD regions are used only for cost display and cloud upload reduction
- LangGraph nodes (Phase 6b) return `dict` of field updates, never mutate state in-place
- Cloud API calls: compute estimated cost from `speech_duration`, print it, confirm before proceeding

## Cost rules (critical ‚Äî never break)
- Default pipeline = $0 (local faster-whisper)
- Two-gate spend model: "key configured" ‚âÝ "provider allowed". `--budget free` rejects any paid provider even if its key is set (F4)
- LLM: `--summarize` / `--clean` default to free Groq. Paid LLM fallback requires `--allow-paid-llm` + cost confirmation ‚Äî no silent escalation

## Testing (Phase 1 Foundations F7)
- Mock at provider/source boundaries, not inside pipeline logic
- Tests are sync (`pytest`, not `pytest-asyncio`) ‚Äî matches the sync core decision
- Fixtures in `tests/fixtures/`: `short_speech.wav`, `short_speech_with_silence.wav`, `tiny_video.mp4`, `golden/`
- Adapter stubs in `tests/stubs/` for `yt-dlp`, providers, LLMs ‚Äî no network in CI
- Integration tests gated on `SSM_INTEGRATION=1`, run in a separate workflow

## Current phase: 0 ‚Äî Skeleton
`src/transcriber/core/`, `sources/`, `formatters/`, `providers/`, `agents/` not yet implemented.
Only `cli.py` (stubbed) and `config.py` exist.
